parameters.text:
=Create a guarded inventory audit and reorder plan from this context.

Run source: {{ $json.run_source }}
Checked at: {{ $json.checked_at }}
Source sheet: {{ $json.source_sheet }}
Valid inventory items: {{ JSON.stringify($json.inventory_items) }}
Invalid rows: {{ JSON.stringify($json.invalid_rows) }}
Recent audit history: {{ JSON.stringify($json.recent_audits) }}
Repeated low item hints: {{ JSON.stringify($json.repeated_low_items) }}

Rules:
- All valid stock values are in KG.
- A valid item is LOW STOCK when stock_kg < 20.
- Replenish each low item to 50 KG. reorder_kg = 50 - current_kg.
- Invalid rows must be included in invalid_rows but must not be treated as zero stock.
- 0 low items: no alert, no approval.
- 1-2 low items: warehouse alert only.
- 3+ low items: warehouse alert plus supplier approval request.
- Repeated shortages in recent audit history should raise risk_level by one level.

You must call log_check exactly once before returning the structured plan. Do not send email yourself. Downstream workflow nodes will validate the plan, send warehouse email, and request supplier approval.

